item.title: Little Help Please
item.dc:creator: @Budda Budda
item.description:
@Budda wrote:

Changing the name of a method call will do nothing but give you errors. Even if you magically changed all the "sytheSpecial"s into “obbyMaulSpecial” it would still only work on the Sythe.

Heres my advice. Rename all the "obbyMaulSpecial back to what they were originally, which I am guessing is “sytheSpecial”. Find the “sytheSpecial” method, which will most likely be shoved in client.java with everything else. Look through it to see anything to do with the ID corrosponding(sp?) to the Sythe, and change it to the Obby Maul. Kay?
